The paper proposes a new framework for multi-hop question answering in web-scale documents, which involves coordinating an implicit extraction module and an explicit reasoning module to gradually build a cognitive graph. This framework is based on BERT and graph neural network and achieves a winning joint F1 score on the HotpotQA fullwiki dataset. Given the focus on natural language processing and machine learning, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
